---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = "ELI Risk Classification Guide | Electrical & Controls Safety";
const description = "How ELI classifies electrical safety content using an industrial likelihood × consequence risk matrix. Every post is assigned a criticality level from L0 to L3.";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
    <style>
      body {
        background: var(--eli-black, #0D0F12);
        color: var(--eli-white, #F2EDE8);
      }

      main {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 3rem 2rem;
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      /* ── PAGE HEADER ── */
      .page-header {
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
        padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--eli-border, #2A3040);
      }

      .page-label {
        font-family: var(--font-mono, 'Share Tech Mono', monospace);
        font-size: 10px;
        color: var(--eli-accent, #E8680A);
        letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

      .page-title {
        font-family: var(--font-display, 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif);
        font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px);
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        color: var(--eli-white, #F2EDE8);
        line-height: 1.1;
        margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
      }

      .page-title span { color: var(--eli-accent, #E8680A); }

      .page-intro {
        font-family: var(--font-body, 'DM Sans', sans-serif);
        font-size: 1rem;
        font-weight: 300;
        color: var(--eli-muted, #8A909E);
        line-height: 1.7;
        max-width: 680px;
      }

      /* ── SECTIONS ── */
      .section {
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
      }

      .section-label {
        font-family: var(--font-mono, 'Share Tech Mono', monospace);
        font-size: 9px;
        color: var(--eli-accent, #E8680A);
        letter-spacing: 0.2em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      }

      .section-label::after {
        content: '';
        flex: 1;
        height: 1px;
        background: var(--eli-border, #2A3040);
      }

      .section-title {
        font-family: var(--font-sub, 'Rajdhani', sans-serif);
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--eli-white, #F2EDE8);
        margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
      }

      .section-body {
        font-family: var(--font-body, 'DM Sans', sans-serif);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        font-weight: 300;
        color: var(--eli-muted, #8A909E);
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      }

      /* ── FULL MATRIX TABLE ── */
      .matrix-wrap { overflow-x: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; }

      .matrix-table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        font-family: var(--font-mono, 'Share Tech Mono', monospace);
        font-size: 12px;
      }

      .matrix-table th {
        background: var(--eli-panel, #1A1E26);
        color: var(--eli-accent, #E8680A);
        font-size: 11px;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        padding: 12px 16px;
        border: 1px solid var(--eli-border, #2A3040);
        text-align: center;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .matrix-table .corner {
        text-align: left;
        color: var(--eli-muted, #8A909E);
        font-size: 10px;
      }

      .matrix-table td {
        padding: 12px 16px;
        border: 1px solid var(--eli-border, #2A3040);
        text-align: center;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        font-size: 13px;
      }

      .row-label {
        background: var(--eli-panel, #1A1E26);
        color: var(--eli-muted, #8A909E);
        text-align: left;
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 400;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .c-l0 { background: rgba(42,122,58,0.20); color: #5DD470; }
      .c-l1 { background: rgba(200,150,10,0.15); color: #E8C040; }
      .c-l2 { background: rgba(232,104,10,0.15); color: #FF8030; }
      .c-l3 { background: rgba(204,34,34,0.15); color: #FF5555; }

      /* ── LEVEL CARDS ── */
      .level-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: 12px;
      }

      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .level-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      }

      .level-card {
        background: var(--eli-panel, #1A1E26);
        border: 1px solid var(--eli-border, #2A3040);
        border-radius: 4px;
        padding: 16px;
        border-top: 2px solid;
      }

      .level-card.l0 { border-top-color: #5DD470; }
      .level-card.l1 { border-top-color: #E8C040; }
      .level-card.l2 { border-top-color: #FF8030; }
      .level-card.l3 { border-top-color: #FF5555; }

      .level-code {
        font-family: var(--font-mono, 'Share Tech Mono', monospace);
        font-size: 9px;
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }

      .level-card.l0 .level-code { color: #5DD470; }
      .level-card.l1 .level-code { color: #E8C040; }
      .level-card.l2 .level-code { color: #FF8030; }
      .level-card.l3 .level-code { color: #FF5555; }

      .level-name {
        font-family: var(--font-sub, 'Rajdhani', sans-serif);
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--eli-white, #F2EDE8);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }

      .level-desc {
        font-family: var(--font-body, 'DM Sans', sans-serif);
        font-size: 0.875rem;
        font-weight: 300;
        color: var(--eli-muted, #8A909E);
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

      .level-examples {
        font-family: var(--font-mono, 'Share Tech Mono', monospace);
        font-size: 9px;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        line-height: 1.9;
        color: var(--eli-muted, #8A909E);
      }

      /* ── CONCLUSION STATE ── */
      .state-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 10px;
      }

      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .state-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      }

      .state-card {
        background: var(--eli-panel, #1A1E26);
        border: 1px solid var(--eli-border, #2A3040);
        border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
        padding: 14px;
      }

      .state-card.safe   { border-left: 3px solid #5DD470; }
      .state-card.hazard { border-left: 3px solid #FF5555; }
      .state-card.neutral{ border-left: 3px solid #8A909E; }

      .state-label {
        font-family: var(--font-mono, 'Share Tech Mono', monospace);
        font-size: 8px;
        letter-spacing: 0.15em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 6px;
      }

      .state-card.safe .state-label   { color: #5DD470; }
      .state-card.hazard .state-label { color: #FF5555; }
      .state-card.neutral .state-label{ color: #8A909E; }

      .state-name {
        font-family: var(--font-sub, 'Rajdhani', sans-serif);
        font-size: 1rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--eli-white, #F2EDE8);
        margin-bottom: 6px;
      }

      .state-desc {
        font-family: var(--font-body, 'DM Sans', sans-serif);
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        font-weight: 300;
        color: var(--eli-muted, #8A909E);
        line-height: 1.6;
      }

      /* ── DISCLAIMER ── */
      .disclaimer {
        background: var(--eli-panel, #1A1E26);
        border: 1px solid var(--eli-border, #2A3040);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--eli-accent, #E8680A);
        border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
        padding: 14px 16px;
        font-family: var(--font-body, 'DM Sans', sans-serif);
        font-size: 0.875rem;
        font-weight: 300;
        color: var(--eli-muted, #8A909E);
        line-height: 1.7;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>

      <div class="page-header">
        <span class="page-label">ELI Content Classification System</span>
        <h1 class="page-title">Risk <span>Classification</span> Guide</h1>
        <p class="page-intro">
          Every post on this blog is classified using the same industrial risk assessment methodology
          used on real worksites. The criticality level determines badge color, visual urgency, and
          how the content should be prioritized by you and your team.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- SECTION 1: MATRIX -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-label">01 — Likelihood × Consequence Matrix</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">How Criticality Is Assigned</h2>
        <p class="section-body">
          Each post is assessed on two axes: how likely the hazard is to occur in a typical industrial
          environment, and what the potential consequence is if it does. The intersection determines
          the criticality level assigned to that content.
        </p>

        <div class="matrix-wrap">
          <table class="matrix-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th class="corner">Likelihood ↓ / Consequence →</th>
                <th>Minor</th>
                <th>Moderate</th>
                <th>Serious Injury</th>
                <th>Fatal</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="row-label">Almost Certain</td>
                <td class="c-l1">L1</td>
                <td class="c-l2">L2</td>
                <td class="c-l3">L3</td>
                <td class="c-l3">L3</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="row-label">Likely</td>
                <td class="c-l0">L0</td>
                <td class="c-l1">L1</td>
                <td class="c-l2">L2</td>
                <td class="c-l3">L3</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="row-label">Possible</td>
                <td class="c-l0">L0</td>
                <td class="c-l0">L0</td>
                <td class="c-l1">L1</td>
                <td class="c-l2">L2</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="row-label">Unlikely</td>
                <td class="c-l0">L0</td>
                <td class="c-l0">L0</td>
                <td class="c-l0">L0</td>
                <td class="c-l1">L1</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- SECTION 2: LEVELS -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-label">02 — Criticality Levels</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">What Each Level Means</h2>
        <div class="level-grid">
          <div class="level-card l0">
            <div class="level-code">L0 — Normal</div>
            <div class="level-name">System OK</div>
            <div class="level-desc">Educational content with no active hazard. Describes correct practice, standards compliance, or foundational knowledge.</div>
            <div class="level-examples">
              Daily Safety Topics<br>
              Correct grounding practice<br>
              LOTO procedures done right<br>
              Code and standards reference
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="level-card l1">
            <div class="level-code">L1 — Advisory</div>
            <div class="level-name">Caution</div>
            <div class="level-desc">A known hazard with low to moderate consequence. Requires awareness and action but typically non-fatal outcome.</div>
            <div class="level-examples">
              Near-miss reports<br>
              Equipment damage incidents<br>
              Procedure deviation warnings<br>
              Advisory safety notices
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="level-card l2">
            <div class="level-code">L2 — Warning</div>
            <div class="level-name">High Risk</div>
            <div class="level-desc">Serious injury potential. Covers arc flash exposure, electrical shock risk, major equipment failure modes, and protection system failures.</div>
            <div class="level-examples">
              Arc flash hazards<br>
              Electrical shock events<br>
              Bonding and grounding failures<br>
              VFD and CT hazards
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="level-card l3">
            <div class="level-code">L3 — Critical</div>
            <div class="level-name">Fatal Risk</div>
            <div class="level-desc">Fatality or multiple serious injuries. Documented deaths, catastrophic system failures, and major incident root cause analyses.</div>
            <div class="level-examples">
              Fatality RCAs<br>
              Electrocution incidents<br>
              Explosion and fire events<br>
              Multi-casualty incidents
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- SECTION 3: CONCLUSION STATE -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-label">03 — Conclusion State</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Post Takeaway Classification</h2>
        <p class="section-body">
          In addition to the criticality level, each post's conclusion is classified to signal whether
          the primary takeaway is a validated safe practice, a failure mode warning, or neutral information.
        </p>
        <div class="state-grid">
          <div class="state-card safe">
            <div class="state-label">Conclusion: Safe</div>
            <div class="state-name">Correct Practice</div>
            <div class="state-desc">The post concludes with a confirmed correct or protected state. "Do this and you are protected." Green takeaway badge.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="state-card hazard">
            <div class="state-label">Conclusion: Hazard</div>
            <div class="state-name">Failure Mode</div>
            <div class="state-desc">The post concludes with a failure mode or do-not-do warning. "This kills people. Do not do this." Red takeaway badge.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="state-card neutral">
            <div class="state-label">Conclusion: Neutral</div>
            <div class="state-name">Informational</div>
            <div class="state-desc">Standards reference, product review, or general awareness. No definitive safe or unsafe conclusion. Gray takeaway badge.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- DISCLAIMER -->
      <div class="disclaimer">
        <strong style="color: var(--eli-white, #F2EDE8); font-weight: 500;">Disclaimer:</strong>
        This classification system is an educational tool to help readers prioritize and contextualize
        safety content. It is not a formal regulatory risk assessment and does not replace site-specific
        hazard assessments, engineering controls, or the requirements of your local Authority Having
        Jurisdiction (AHJ). Always refer to applicable codes and standards including CEC, NEC, CSA Z462,
        and NFPA 70E for compliance requirements.
      </div>

    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
